# ⚡ Introduction to JavaScript

> First steps into JavaScript programming and understanding how it adds interactivity to modern web pages.

---

# 📖 Overview

This activity introduces **JavaScript**, the programming language responsible for making websites interactive.

Unlike HTML, which defines the structure of a webpage, and CSS, which controls its appearance, JavaScript allows web pages to react to user actions, manipulate content dynamically, and execute programming logic directly in the browser.

In this practice, I learned how to create an external JavaScript file and connect it to HTML pages, preparing my website for future interactive features.

---

# 🎯 Learning Objectives

During this activity I learned how to:

- Understand the purpose of JavaScript
- Differentiate HTML, CSS, and JavaScript
- Create an external JavaScript file
- Link JavaScript to HTML
- Execute JavaScript inside the browser
- Prepare a website for interactive functionality

